title: Appointments to Hospital Authority announced
content_text:
p>
    The Government announced today (March 25) the re-appointment of one serving 
    member and the appointment of three new members to the Hospital Authority, 
    with effect from April 1, 2011.  Mr Lawrence Lee Kam-hung is re-appointed for one year.  The new members are Ms Chiang Lai-yuen, Mr Pang Yiu-kai and Professor 
    Maurice Yap Keng-hung. They are appointed for two years. Following is a

brief biography of the new members: Ms Chiang Lai-yuen is currently the Chief Executive Officer of a listed 
    company. She is also a member of the Council of both the Hong Kong 
    University of Science and Technology and the Open University of Hong Kong, 
    and a member of the Standing Committee on Directorate Salaries and 
    Conditions of Service of the Government of the Hong Kong SAR. Mr Pang Yiu-kai is the Chief Executive of a listed real estate group. He is 
    now serving as the Chairman of the Council of the Hong Kong Institute of

now serving as the Chairman of the Council of the Hong Kong Institute of 
    Education, the Joint Committee on Student Finance and the Quality Education 
    Fund Steering Committee. He is also a member of the Exchange Fund Advisory 
    Committee and the Standing Commission on Civil Service Salaries and 
    Conditions of Service. Professor Maurice Yap Keng-hung is currently a Chair Professor at the School 
    of Optometry of the Hong Kong Polytechnic University. He has been appointed 
    as the Dean of the Faculty of Health and Social Sciences of the Hong Kong

as the Dean of the Faculty of Health and Social Sciences of the Hong Kong 
    Polytechnic University with effect from April 1, 2011. He is also serving as 
    a member of the Supplementary Medical Professions Council and the Hong Kong 
    Paralympians Fund Management Committee. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, welcomed the new members to 
    the Authority. He also thanked the outgoing members, Professor Lai Kar-neng, 
    Mr Peter Lo Chi-lik, Mr Charles Peter Mok and Professor George Woo, for

their advice and contributions to the Hospital Authority over the years. They will retire from the Hospital Authority with effect from April 1, 2011. The Hospital Authority, from April 1, 2011, will comprise a chairman, 22 non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the Hospital Authority.
